90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/vGSFATL</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[vidadobl6]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Has anyone else seen this? My sense is that the first contemporary Lord of the Flies situation is going to go down in Phoenix.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Sv1k7MP</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/d68OQlZ.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Sv1k7MP</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[trustfallaccident]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Chemo port removed yesterday!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/CodpxwI</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/nt6BolR.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>They didn’t let me keep it, but here it is! All the specks are from each time I got stabbed, for 12 rounds. What that meant for me was chemo infusions once a week for twelve weeks, and targeted antibody therapy once every three weeks for a year.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/gGDYOrf.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is how it’s installed. The catheter goes directly into the main inlet vein of the heart. If it were just an arm IV, the risk is it could leak into the surrounding tissue which can damage it, since it’s such nasty stuff. 

I was very lucky that the kind of breast cancer I got is common and very well understood, and has incredibly effective drugs to fight it. Chemo and surgery was 100% effective, and I’m cancer free now! My doc even uses the word “cured,” not just in remission. 

I thought the device was nifty, so I wanted to share. Cheers, friends!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/CodpxwI</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[tomicGoober]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>It is cute</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/HCHjYzp</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/aHu0zuT.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/HCHjYzp</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[TheBigLetdown]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>These dancers from India are on a whole other level</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/LezBbVu</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/HsxbkJf.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/LezBbVu</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[mfrybeasley]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Who will win?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/KeFrID9</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UU6e5qr.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/KeFrID9</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[AgeingAss]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Celebrating small victories!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/01PNUWt</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/n4cnkmD.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Whoo-hoo! And I did a short walk around the block today!

